<paragraph blockId="6.[170,663,1325,1350]" box="[170,663,1325,1350]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading box="[170,663,1325,1350]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="5">
<taxonomicName authority="Kotov &amp; Stifter, 2004" authorityName="Kotov &amp; Stifter" authorityYear="2004" box="[170,663,1325,1350]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Ilyocryptidae" genus="Ilyocryptus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plumosus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,663,1325,1350]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,414,1325,1350]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ilyocryptus plumosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kotov, A. A. &amp; Stifter, P." box="[420,663,1325,1350]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="193 - 198" refId="ref4584" refString="Kotov, A. A. &amp; Stifter, P. 2004. Notes on the genus Ilyocryptus Sars, 1862 (Cladocera: Anomopoda: Ilyocryptidae). 1. Ilyocryptus plumosus sp. n., a primitive Neotropical member of the I. spinifer - group. Arthropoda Selecta, 13 (4): 193 - 198." type="journal article" year="2004">Kotov &amp; Štifter, 2004</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[170,794,1389,1871]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ovoid body, dorsal keel well developed, molting incomplete; setae on the posterior margin of valves without spine but armed with setulae. Head triangular shaped, fornices prominent; spine on the second segment of endopodite of antenna shorter than mid length of the third segment. Postabdomen large, preanal part shorter than postanal; marginal denticles of preanal part with regular morphology, decreasing of length towards anal part; 17-20 marginal spines which increase in length towards distal part of postabdomen; distalmost part of postanal part with 3-6 rudimentary lateral setae, up four long lateral setae about 5-7 times longer than marginal spines; a long “gap” between proximalmost lateral seta and anal margin. basal spines on the postabdominal claw of different length.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[170,794,1910,2131]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,305,1910,1935]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Comments:</emphasis>
This is the first report of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kotov &amp; Stifter" authorityYear="2004" box="[570,794,1910,1935]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Ilyocryptidae" genus="Ilyocryptus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plumosus">
<emphasis box="[570,794,1910,1935]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ilyocryptus plumosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[196,258,1943,1968]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.The description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kotov &amp; Stifter" authorityYear="2004" box="[470,591,1943,1968]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Ilyocryptidae" genus="Ilyocryptus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plumosus">
<emphasis box="[470,591,1943,1968]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">I. plumosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was based on materials sampled in 
<collectingCountry box="[367,481,1976,2001]" name="Venezuela" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[534,650,1976,2001]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
. In 
<collectingCountry box="[683,745,1976,2001]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Brazil</collectingCountry>
,this species is rare and only known for the Serra do Cabral hills, state of 
<collectingRegion box="[326,471,2041,2066]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[487,571,2041,2066]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="5.[94,153,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[114,1398,333,2043]" captionTargetId="figure-49@5.[113,1398,332,2044]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 3. Geographic distribution Ilyocryptidae Smirnov 1976 emend.Smirnov,1992 taxa of Brazil. (A) Ilyocryptus cuneatus brasiliensis.(B) Ilyocryptus paranaensis inarmatus.(C) Ilyocryptus paranaensis paranaensis.(D) Ilyocryptus plumosus.(E)Ilyocryptus silvaeducensis paraensis.(F) Ilyocryptus sarsi.(G) Ilyocryptus spinifer." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4613808" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4613808/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). The complete description of this species, including the thoracic appendages, can be found in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kotov, A. A. &amp; Stifter, P." box="[411,648,2106,2131]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="193 - 198" refId="ref4584" refString="Kotov, A. A. &amp; Stifter, P. 2004. Notes on the genus Ilyocryptus Sars, 1862 (Cladocera: Anomopoda: Ilyocryptidae). 1. Ilyocryptus plumosus sp. n., a primitive Neotropical member of the I. spinifer - group. Arthropoda Selecta, 13 (4): 193 - 198." type="journal article" year="2004">Kotov &amp; Štifter (2004)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
